<div style="margin-bottom:30px;"><i><b>What are our thoughts on active funds?</b></i></div>
  
<p><b>We are not advisors and therefore have no opinions; however, the data speaks for itself. </b></p>
  <p>According to S&P Global, 98% of all active funds underperform the S&P500 Index by 2.2% on average after taxes over a 20 year period. <a href="https://www.spglobal.com/spdji/en/documents/brochure/spiva-after-tax-infographic.pdf">Link</a> Over a 30 year period it would be even worse!</p>

<p><b>What does this mean?</b></p>
  <p>Below is an illustration of the differences of what your typical result would be under professional management or without an advisor invested in active funds. This example starts with $500,000 - as you can see the affect yourself over a 30 year period. </p>

